any pod should be able to communicate with any other pod in the same collector, to protect some pods communicating with some other pods, we use network policies.
after setting ingress rules, we dont need to set egress rules as it is the response to the incoming pod.

specify podSelector, policyTypes and ingress under spec section in the NetworkPolicy file, specify namespace under ingress section.
if a server is external of the cluster, we use ipBlock to allow the connection from a pod outside of the current collector.
as soon as you apply policies to a pod, it kinda blocks other pods ingress or exgress, that's why we need to manually allows it.
